preamble.title: cardanofoundation/cardano-ibc
preamble.description: The project involves implementing the Inter-Blockchain Communication (IBC) protocol on the Cardano main chain using Aiken.

cardano/transaction/OutputReference.title: OutputReference
cardano/transaction/OutputReference.description:
An `OutputReference` is a unique reference to an output on-chain. The `output_index`
 corresponds to the position in the output list of the transaction (identified by its id)
 that produced that output

fields.title: denom
fields.description: the token denomination to be transferred

fields.title: amount
fields.description: the token amount to be transferred

fields.title: sender
fields.description: the sender address

fields.title: receiver
fields.description: the recipient address on the destination chain

fields.title: memo
fields.description: optional memo

ibc/core/ics_003_connection_semantics/ty.title: Counterparty
ibc/core/ics_003_connection_semantics/ty.description: Counterparty defines the counterparty chain associated with a connection end.

ibc/core/ics_004/types/channel/Channel.title: Channel
ibc/core/ics_004/types/channel/Channel.description:
Channel defines pipeline for exactly-once packet delivery between specific
 modules on separate blockchains, which has at least one end capable of
 sending packets and one end capable of receiving packets.

fields.title: state
fields.description: current state of the channel end

fields.title: ordering
fields.description: whether the channel is ordered or unordered

fields.title: counterparty
fields.description: counterparty channel end

fields.title: connection_hops
fields.description:
list of connection identifiers, in order, along which packets sent on
 this channel will travel

fields.title: version
fields.description: opaque channel version, which is agreed upon during the handshake

ibc/core/ics_004/types/counterparty/Chan.title: ChannelCounterparty
ibc/core/ics_004/types/counterparty/Chan.description: ChannelCounterparty defines a channel end counterparty

fields.title: port_id
fields.description: port on the counterparty chain which owns the other end of the channel.

fields.title: channel_id
fields.description: channel end on the counterparty chain

ibc/core/ics_004/types/order/Order.title: Order
ibc/core/ics_004/types/order/Order.description: Order defines if a channel is ORDERED or UNORDERED

anyOf.title: Unordered
anyOf.description: packets can be delivered in any order, which may differ from the order in which they were sent.

anyOf.title: Ordered
anyOf.description: packets are delivered exactly in the order which they were sent

ibc/core/ics_004/types/packet/Packet.title: Packet
ibc/core/ics_004/types/packet/Packet.description: Packet defines a type that carries data across different chains through IBC

fields.title: sequence
fields.description:
number corresponds to the order of sends and receives, where a Packet
 with an earlier sequence number must be sent and received before a Packet
 with a later sequence number.

fields.title: source_port
fields.description: identifies the port on the sending chain.

fields.title: source_channel
fields.description: identifies the channel end on the sending chain.

fields.title: destination_port
fields.description: identifies the port on the receiving chain.

fields.title: destination_channel
fields.description: identifies the channel end on the receiving chain.

fields.title: data
fields.description: actual opaque bytes transferred directly to the application module

fields.title: timeout_height
fields.description: block height after which the packet times out

fields.title: timeout_timestamp
fields.description: block timestamp (in nanoseconds) after which the packet times out

ibc/core/ics_004/types/state/ChannelStat.title: ChannelState
ibc/core/ics_004/types/state/ChannelStat.description:
ChannelState defines if a channel is in one of the following states:
 CLOSED, INIT, TRYOPEN, OPEN or UNINITIALIZED.

anyOf.title: Init
anyOf.description: A channel has just started the opening handshake.

anyOf.title: TryOpen
anyOf.description: A channel has acknowledged the handshake step on the counterparty chain.

anyOf.title: Open
anyOf.description:
A channel has completed the handshake. Open channels are
 ready to send and receive packets.

anyOf.title: Closed
anyOf.description: A channel has been closed and can no longer be used to send or receive packets.
